ficate chains\n- OcspResponseWrapper instances for OCSP responses\n- Private key method providers\n- QUIC-specific certificate chains\n\nThe ContextImpl provides customVerifyCertChain and customVerifyCertChainForQuic methods that delegate to the cert_validator_ instance. ClientContextImpl (in source/common/tls/client_context_impl.h) and ServerContextImpl (in source/common/tls/server_context_impl.h) extend ContextImpl with client and server-specific functionality.\n\n## OCSP Response Parsing and Stapling\nThe OCSP implementation in source/common/tls/ocsp/ includes:\n- OcspResponse and BasicOcspResponse classes representing parsed OCSP response structures\n- OcspResponseWrapperImpl providing owned access to OCSP responses with methods like matchesCertificate and isExpired\n- Asn1OcspUtility for parsing OCSP responses from DER format using methods like parseOcspResponse, parseResponseStatus, and parseBasicOcspResponse\n- Asn1Utility (in source/common/tls/ocsp/asn1_utility.h) providing low-level ASN.1 DER parsing utilities\n\nServerContextImpl implements OCSP stapling through ocspStapleAction method, selecting stapling policies (LenientStapling, StrictStapling, MustStaple) and managing OCSP response attachment to TLS handshakes.\n\n## SPIFFE Validator Extension\nThe SPIFFEValidator in source/extensions/transport_sockets/tls/cert_validator/spiffe/spiffe_validator.h provides specialized validation for SPIFFE certificates, including trust bundle store management, certificate precheck validation, and SAN matching specific to SPIFFE URIs.\n\n## Validation Flow\nThe validation flow proceeds as: CertValidator.doVerifyCertChain (entry point) → DefaultCertValidator.doVerifyCertChain (implementation) → verifyCertAndUpdateStatus → verifyCertificate (which calls verifySubjectAltName and matchSubjectAltName) → X509 verification using OpenSSL/BoringSSL APIs. OCSP responses are validated through OcspResponseWrapperImpl.matchesCertificate, which extracts certificate serial numbers and matches against OCSP response data.\n\nUtility functions in source/common/tls/cert_validator/utility.h provide helper functions like setIgnoreCertificateExpiration for testing scenarios and other X509 store operations."
